        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-1 mb-4">How Much Does iTalki Cost in 2026? Full Pricing Guide</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500">iTalki charges less than most people expect. Community tutors start at just $3 per hour. Professional teachers offer structured lessons from $15 per hour. Here is the complete breakdown of what you will actually pay in 2026.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between flex-wrap gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg">Starting Price</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-700">$3/hr</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Community tutors</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg">Professional Lessons</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-700">$15/hr</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Certified teachers</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg">Top Teachers</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-700">$60/hr</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">Maximum rate</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <AdUnit />

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Understanding iTalki's Two-Tier Pricing System</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">One of the most common questions before signing up for iTalki is simply this: how much does it cost? The honest answer is that iTalki does not have a fixed price. Instead, it uses a flexible marketplace model where every tutor sets their own rate.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">This means you can find lessons for as little as $3 per hour or pay up to $60 per hour for the most experienced teachers. What you pay depends entirely on the type of tutor you choose and how popular they are.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki divides its tutors into two main categories. Each category has a different pricing range and suits different learning needs:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 mb-6">
        <li><strong>Community Tutors ($3 to $15 per hour)</strong>: Informal, conversational practice with friendly native speakers. These tutors are great for building confidence and cultural exchange.</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Teachers ($15 to $60 per hour)</strong>: Certified educators with structured lesson plans. They are ideal for exam preparation, business English, and formal learning goals.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">By the end of this guide, you will know exactly what iTalki costs and which tutor type fits your budget. If you want a deeper look at the platform first, read our full <a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">iTalki review</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Community Tutor Pricing</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Community Tutors on iTalki are native or fluent speakers who offer conversational practice. They do not necessarily hold formal teaching certifications, but many have years of experience helping learners improve their speaking skills.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The prices below reflect what most Community Tutors charge in 2026. Every tutor sets their own rate, so these are guide ranges rather than fixed prices.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-slate-900/40">
              <th class="p-3 font-bold border border-slate-700">Tutor Type</th>
              <th class="p-3 font-bold border border-slate-700">Average Price/Hour</th>
              <th class="p-3 font-bold border border-slate-700">Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700">New Community Tutors</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700 font-bold text-green-700">$3 to $5</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700">Very affordable. Great for absolute beginners.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-slate-900/40">
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700">Established Community Tutors</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700 font-bold text-green-700">$5 to $10</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700">Budget-friendly. Most popular price range.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700">Popular Community Tutors</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700 font-bold text-green-700">$10 to $15</td>
              <td class="p-3 border border-slate-700">Premium tier. High demand, excellent reviews.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Key things to know about Community Tutors:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 mb-6">
        <li>Trial lessons are often available at a discount or for free. Always check individual profiles.</li>
        <li>Some tutors offer small package discounts if you book multiple lessons at once.</li>
        <li>Lesson plans and curriculum materials are not included. You decide the conversation topics.</li>
        <li>Best for: Casual conversation practice, cultural exchange, building speaking confidence.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Professional Teacher Pricing</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Professional Teachers on iTalki hold at least one verified teaching qualification. This includes certificates like CELTA, TESOL, or equivalent qualifications. They follow a structured curriculum and prepare lesson materials for each session.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Because these teachers invest significantly in their training, their rates are higher. However, you get what you pay for: structured lessons, homework, and a clear learning path.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
