      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 mb-6">
        <li>Prices vary based on the teacher's qualifications, experience, and demand.</li>
        <li>Some teachers offer 5 to 10 percent discounts on multi-lesson packages.</li>
        <li>First trial lessons are often available at a reduced rate. Check the teacher's profile for current offers.</li>
        <li>Best for: Structured learning, IELTS or TOEFL preparation, business English, academic English.</li>
      </ul>

      <AdUnit />

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">How to Calculate Your Monthly iTalki Costs</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Working out your monthly iTalki cost is straightforward. You only need two numbers: your hourly rate and how many lessons you plan to take each week. Here is a simple step-by-step method.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Step 1: Choose Your Tutor Type</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <li>Community Tutor: Average rate around $8 per hour</li>
        <li>Professional Teacher: Average rate around $20 per hour</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">Step 2: Estimate Your Weekly Lessons</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <li>1 lesson per week = 4 lessons per month</li>
        <li>2 lessons per week = 8 lessons per month</li>
        <li>3 lessons per week = 12 lessons per month</li>
      </ul>

