        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800"><strong>Note:</strong> These are estimates. Actual prices vary by individual tutor. Some tutors offer package discounts that can reduce your monthly cost by 5 to 10 percent. Always check current prices on the tutor's profile before booking.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">5 Ways to Reduce Your iTalki Costs</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">You do not need to spend a fortune to improve your English on iTalki. Here are five practical strategies to get the most value from the platform while keeping your costs low.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">1. Start with Community Tutors</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">If you are new to iTalki, begin with Community Tutors at $3 to $10 per hour. This lets you practise conversation without committing to expensive professional lessons. Once you build your confidence, you can decide if you need a structured curriculum.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">2. Book Trial Lessons First</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Most tutors on iTalki offer a discounted or even free first lesson. Use these trial sessions to find a tutor you connect with before buying a full package. This is one of the easiest ways to save money while testing the platform.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">3. Buy Multi-Lesson Packages</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Several professional teachers offer 5 to 10 percent discounts when you book five or more lessons at once. If you have found a tutor you like, asking about package pricing can reduce your cost per lesson significantly.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">4. Try Multiple Tutors Before Committing</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Do not feel pressured to stick with the first tutor you try. Book trial lessons with three or four different tutors at different price points. This helps you find the best value combination of price, teaching style, and personality.</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-3">5. Watch for iTalki Promotions</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki occasionally runs promotions where you receive bonus credits when you purchase a package. These promotions can effectively give you one or two extra lessons for free. Follow iTalki's social media or check their website for current offers.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">iTalki Cost Compared to Other Platforms</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">How does iTalki stack up against other popular tutoring platforms? Here is a side-by-side comparison of pricing across iTalki, Preply, Cambly, and Verbling. All prices are approximate 2026 rates.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
